acceptOwnership().details: The new owner accepts the ownership transfer.

params._unstakeDelaySec: - the unstake delay for this entity. Can only be increased.

createAccount(bytes32,bytes32,bytes).details: Salted deterministic deployment using create2 and a specific logic UpgradableMSCA implementation.      Since UpgradableMSCA is only a bare minimum account and tx/userOp (including installPlugin) is gated by      either userOpValidationFunction (most of our use cases) or runtimeValidationFunction,      we require the user to install at least one plugin (e.g. ACL) that can provide validationFunction during account deployment.      No dependencies or hooks can be injected during this plugin installation, so for a full installation of more complicated plugins,      please call installPlugin via a separate tx/userOp after account deployment.

params._initializingData: abi.encode(address[] plugins, bytes32[] manifestHashes, bytes[] pluginInstallData)
params._salt: salt that allows for deterministic deployment
params._sender: sender of the account deployment tx, it could be set to owner (either an address or public key hash). If you don't have the owner information during account creation,                please use something unique, consistent and private to yourself.

getAddress(bytes32,bytes32,bytes).details: Pre-compute the counterfactual address prior to calling createAccount.

params._salt: salt that allows for deterministic deployment

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

pendingOwner().details: Returns the address of the pending owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Starts the ownership transfer of the contract to a new account. Replaces the pending transfer if there is one. Can only be called by the current owner.

params._withdrawAddress: the address to send withdrawn value.

addStake(uint32).notice: Add stake for this entity.This method can also carry eth value to add to the current stake.

unlockStake().notice: Unlock the stake, in order to withdraw it.This entity can't serve requests once unlocked, until it calls addStake again.

withdrawStake(address).notice: Withdraw the entire entity's stake.stake must be unlocked first (and then wait for the unstakeDelay to be over).
